# JavaScript

## Style

- 2-space indentation, single quotes, semicolons
- Prefer `const` over `let`; avoid `var`
- Trailing commas in multi-line objects and arrays
- Small, single-purpose functions; prefer functional patterns

## Error Handling

```javascript
// ✅ Return defaults for expected failures; log for debugging
try {
  const data = await fetch(url);
  if (!data.ok) return null;
  return await data.json();
} catch (e) {
  console.error('Fetch failed:', e);
  return null;
}
```

## Data & DOM

- Validate structure before accessing nested properties
- Use optional chaining (`?.`) and nullish coalescing (`??`)
- Use `fetch` with `cache: 'no-store'` when fresh data is required
- Use `querySelector` / `getElementById`; prefer `insertAdjacentHTML` over `innerHTML` for appends
- Use event delegation for dynamic content

## Dates

- Store UTC in JSON; format display with `Intl.DateTimeFormat` and explicit timezone
- Use `America/New_York` for all user-facing times in this app

## Comments

- Self-documenting names over comments
- Comment non-obvious business logic (timezone transforms, traffic impact rules)
